Technical Whitepaper: Booster Fusion Algorithm (BoA)

A Framework for Stabilizing Complex Multi-Algorithm Systems Through Auxiliary Intelligence

---

Executive Summary

The Booster Fusion Algorithm (BoA) represents a paradigm shift in artificial intelligence systems engineering, addressing the critical challenge of maintaining stability and coherence in complex environments where multiple independent algorithms operate concurrently. Developed by the QUENNE Research Institute in Saitama, Japan, BoA introduces an auxiliary intelligence layer that functions as a "conductor" of algorithmic ecosystems, dynamically regulating interactions to ensure reliable, consistent system performance.

Traditional AI system design focuses on optimizing individual algorithms, often overlooking the emergent behaviors and instability that arise when multiple intelligent components interact. BoA addresses this fundamental gap through adaptive coordination mechanisms, real-time stability assessment, and intelligent fusion parameter adjustment. This whitepaper presents the complete technical framework, implementation methodology, and empirical validation of BoA as a foundational technology for next-generation AI systems requiring guaranteed stability under increasing complexity.

