3.2 Core Design Principles

3.2.1 Auxiliary Intelligence Principle

BoA operates as a non-invasive layer, requiring no modification to existing algorithms. This ensures backward compatibility and reduces integration complexity.

3.2.2 Separation of Concerns

Clear separation between:

· Computation: Primary algorithms performing domain-specific tasks
· Coordination: BoA managing interactions and stability
· Fusion: Integration of diverse outputs into coherent decisions

3.2.3 Real-Time Responsiveness

Architecture optimized for:

· Latency: <10ms processing time (99th percentile)
· Throughput: Up to 1,000 fused decisions/second
· Adaptation speed: <50ms response to stability threats

3.2.4 Graceful Degradation

Progressive fallback strategies ensure system functionality under extreme conditions:

1. Normal operation: Full adaptive capabilities
2. Degraded mode: Conservative fusion with reduced adaptation
3. Safe mode: Fixed weights, minimal functionality
4. Bypass mode: Direct algorithm outputs with monitoring only

3.3 Component Architecture

3.3.1 Stability Orchestrator

The central coordination component responsible for:

· Coherence assessment: Real-time calculation of stability metrics
· Parameter optimization: Dynamic weight adjustment
· Strategy selection: Adaptive fusion method selection
· State management: Tracking system stability transitions

3.3.2 Model Registry

Comprehensive database of algorithm characteristics:

```python
AlgorithmProfile = {
    "algorithm_id": "uuid",
    "type": "perception|control|prediction|optimization",
    "performance_characteristics": {...},
    "interaction_constraints": {...},
    "adaptation_parameters": {...}
}
```

3.3.3 Adaptation Engine

Implements multiple adaptation strategies:

· Confidence-weighted adjustment: Based on algorithm confidence scores
· Reinforcement learning: Long-term stability optimization
· Bayesian optimization: Uncertainty-aware parameter tuning
· Conservative fallback: Risk-averse coordination under uncertainty

3.3.4 Fault Detection System

Multi-layered anomaly detection:

1. Statistical anomaly detection: Mahalanobis distance-based outlier detection
2. Temporal consistency checking: Output sequence validation
3. Cross-algorithm verification: Consistency across multiple algorithms
4. Resource monitoring: CPU, memory, and latency anomaly detection

