8. Security & Safety Considerations

8.1 Security Architecture

8.1.1 Authentication & Authorization

· JWT-based authentication: Secure API access
· Role-based access control: Fine-grained permission management
· API key rotation: Regular credential updates
· Mutual TLS: Secure inter-component communication

8.1.2 Data Protection

· Encryption at rest: AES-256 for configuration and logs
· Secure memory management: Zeroization of sensitive data
· Input validation: Comprehensive sanitization of all inputs
· Secure logging: No sensitive data in logs

8.1.3 Threat Mitigation

· Rate limiting: Protection against denial-of-service attacks
· Anomaly detection: Behavioral analysis for malicious patterns
· Regular audits: Security assessment and penetration testing
· Patch management: Regular security updates

8.2 Safety Framework

8.2.1 Fail-Safe Design

1. Watchdog timers: System reset on unresponsiveness
2. Heartbeat monitoring: Continuous liveness verification
3. Graceful degradation: Progressive functionality reduction
4. Safe state transition: Controlled mode changes

8.2.2 Verification & Validation

· Formal methods: Mathematical verification of critical components
· Simulation testing: Extensive scenario-based testing
· Field validation: Real-world deployment validation
· Third-party assessment: Independent safety evaluation

8.2.3 Regulatory Compliance

· Functional safety: IEC 61508, ISO 26262, DO-178C compliance
· AI ethics: IEEE P7000 series alignment
· Data privacy: GDPR, CCPA compliance
· Industry standards: Domain-specific regulatory requirements

8.3 Ethical Considerations

8.3.1 Transparency

· Explainable adaptation: Clear rationale for all interventions
